How do I structure the response format for a json_schema in Open AI's API, to be an object with only a single property "keywords", which is an array of strings?
To structure a JSON schema for an object with a single property "keywords" that's an array of strings, you would format it like this:

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "keywords": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["keywords"]
}
```

This schema:
- Specifies it's an object (`"type": "object"`)
- Defines a single property called "keywords"
- Specifies that "keywords" is an array (`"type": "array"`)
- Specifies that each item in the array must be a string (`"items": {"type": "string"}`)
- Makes the "keywords" property required

When used with the OpenAI API, this will ensure responses are formatted like:
```json
{
  "keywords": ["word1", "word2", "word3"]
}
```
